CM ============================================================
CM Arcanum Reference Deck — Half-Wave Dipole
CM V-REAL-001 in docs/nec-import/validation.md
CM ============================================================
CM Classic center-fed half-wave dipole in free space.
CM This is the foundational validation case for Arcanum.
CM If this deck does not parse and simulate correctly,
CM nothing else is worth testing.
CM
CM Geometry:
CM   Frequency:    300 MHz  (lambda = 1.0 m)
CM   Total length: 0.5 m    (lambda/2)
CM   Each arm:     0.25 m
CM   Wire radius:  0.001 m  (1 mm)
CM   Segments:     11 (odd, so center segment is segment 6)
CM   Orientation:  z-axis, center at origin
CM
CM Source:
CM   Delta-gap voltage source, tag 1, segment 6, 1V
CM   Segment 6 is the center segment — spans z = 0 approximately
CM
CM Expected results (Phase 3 validation, V-SOLVE-003):
CM   Input impedance: Z_in ≈ 73 + j42.5 Ω (classical thin-wire result)
CM   Tolerance: ±5 Ω on both real and imaginary parts
CM   Note: reactance sensitive to exact length and radius
CM
CM Expected results (Phase 4 validation, V-PAT-001, V-DIR-002):
CM   E-plane pattern: F(theta) = cos(pi/2 * cos(theta)) / sin(theta)
CM   H-plane pattern: omnidirectional
CM   Maximum directivity: 1.64 (2.15 dBi)
CM
CM Provenance: Synthesized by ORI for Arcanum validation.
CM   Parameters chosen to match V-REAL-001 conditions exactly.
CM   Classical result from Balanis, Antenna Theory, Chapter 4.
CE
CM ============================================================
CM GEOMETRY
CM ============================================================
CM Tag 1: Half-wave dipole along z-axis, 11 segments
CM   From z = -0.25 m to z = +0.25 m
GW 1 11 0.0 0.0 -0.25 0.0 0.0 0.25 0.001
GE 0
CM ============================================================
CM SIMULATION PARAMETERS
CM ============================================================
CM Delta-gap voltage source at center segment (tag 1, segment 6)
EX 0 1 6 0 1.0 0.0
CM
CM Frequency: 300 MHz = c/lambda = 299.792458 MHz/m * 1m
FR 0 1 0 0 299.792458 0.0
CM
CM Far-field radiation pattern, 5 degree grid, full sphere
RP 0 37 73 1000 0.0 0.0 5.0 5.0 0.0
CM
EN
